{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/post/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/","result":{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Permainan Pachinko Jepang Menuju Kepunahan?","content":"<p><em>Entertainment</em> dari negara Jepang tidak melulu hanya berkisar soal <em>video game</em> (dimana mereka merupakan pemain penting di industri itu), anime, manga ataupun J-Pop <em>culture</em> populer seperti lagu dan film.</p>\n<p>Walaupun tentu sulit dibantah kalau J-Pop <em>culture</em> yang terkenal di seantero dunia adalah elemen-elemen tadi, namun untuk pasar hiburan lokal ada pula hal-hal yang sama populernya dengan <em>video game</em> atau dorama tapi tidak begitu terdengar reputasinya hingga mendunia. Seperti misalnya Kamishibai; wayang kertas era sebelum Perang Dunia Kedua yang mempopulerkan <a href=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/mengenal-gegege-no-kitaro-anime-yang-akan-menggantikan-slot-tv-dragon-ball-super/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">GeGeGe no Kitaro</a> sebagai manga dan anime.</p>\n<p>Atau Pachinko; sebuah mesin hiburan yang mungkin cocok juga disebut sebagai nenek moyang <em>arcade box video game.</em></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Pachinko. Apa itu?</h2>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46201\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46201\" data-attachment-id=\"46201\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo-7/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko7.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Satu contoh dari ribuan model mesin pachinko. Sumber: Wiktionary\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Satu contoh dari ribuan model mesin pachinko. Sumber: Wiktionary&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko7-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko7.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46201\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko7.jpg\" alt=\"Satu contoh dari ribuan model mesin pachinko. Sumber: Wiktionary\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko7.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko7-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46201\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Satu contoh dari ribuan model mesin pachinko. Sumber: Wiktionary</p></div></p>\n<p>Secara prinsip, mesin Pachinko adalah sebuah mesin judi , karena adanya aspek untung-untungan saat memainkan mesin tersebut. Berbeda dengan mesin <em>arcade video game</em> yang membutuhkan ‘<em>set of skills</em>’ untuk memenangi <em>game,</em> di pachinko, faktor keberuntungan sangat berpengaruh untuk menang. Tidak terlalu dibutuhkan keahlian khusus untuk memainkan pachinko karena <em>‘gameplay’</em> yang ada memang sederhana dan memerlukan keberuntungan.</p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46200\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46200\" data-attachment-id=\"46200\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo-6/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko6.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Contoh layar di mesin pachinko. Sumber: Bloomberg\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Contoh layar di mesin pachinko. Sumber: Bloomberg&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko6-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko6.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46200\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko6.jpg\" alt=\"Contoh layar di mesin pachinko. Sumber: Bloomberg\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko6.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko6-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46200\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Contoh layar di mesin pachinko. Sumber: Bloomberg</p></div></p>\n<p>Mesin pachinko awalnya bukanlah buatan Jepang. Sama seperti (olahraga nasional Jepang) <em>baseball</em>, pachinko aslinya merupakan produk dari Amerika Serikat. Di era 1920an, mesin ini ditujukan sebagai mainan anak-anak dengan nama “<em>Corinth Game”</em>. Nama itu berangsur-angsur berubah menjadi “Pachinko” juga karena pengaruh anak-anak; di mana mesin <em>Corinth</em> menimbulkan bunyi &#8220;<em>pachi pachi&#8221; </em>(bunyi saat dua atau lebih benda metal beradu di telinga orang Jepang) sehingga lama kelamaan orang menyebut mesin <em>Corinth</em> sebagai “pachinko”.</p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46196\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46196\" data-attachment-id=\"46196\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo-2/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko2.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Nenek moyang mesin pachinko modern. Sumber: The-Saleroom\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Nenek moyang mesin pachinko modern. Sumber: The-Saleroom&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko2-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko2.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46196\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko2.jpg\" alt=\"Nenek moyang mesin pachinko modern. Sumber: The-Saleroom\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko2.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko2-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46196\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Nenek moyang mesin pachinko modern. Sumber: The-Saleroom</p></div></p>\n<p>Mesin pachinko bisa pula disebut sebagai “<em>Vertical Pinball</em>”. Bedanya? Selain <em>form factor</em> yang berdiri tegak lurus (berbeda dengan <em>pinball</em> yang lebih horizontal diagonal), ‘bola besi’ yang digunakan di pachinko tidak berjumlah satu tapi banyak. Ukurannya juga jauh lebih kecil. Saat mengarahkan bola-bola besi kecil pachinko ke <em>slot jackpot</em> akan terdengar bunyi ‘pachi pachi’ yang khas sehingga tempat dimana ada mesin pachinko biasanya akan selalu terdengar riuh. Suara dari bola-bola besi mini ber-diameter 11mm yang beradu satu sama lain.</p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46203\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46203\" data-attachment-id=\"46203\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo-9/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko9.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Deretan mesin pinball. Sumber : HomeLeisureDirect\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Deretan mesin pinball. Sumber : HomeLeisureDirect&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko9-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko9.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46203\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko9.jpg\" alt=\"Deretan mesin pinball. Sumber : HomeLeisureDirect\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko9.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko9-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46203\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Deretan mesin pinball. Sumber : HomeLeisureDirect</p></div></p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46195\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46195\" data-attachment-id=\"46195\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko1.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Bola-bola mesin pachinko. Sumber: JapanTimes\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Bola-bola mesin pachinko. Sumber: JapanTimes&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko1-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko1.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46195\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko1.jpg\" alt=\"Bola-bola mesin pachinko. Sumber: JapanTimes\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko1.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko1-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46195\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Bola-bola mesin pachinko. Sumber: JapanTimes</p></div></p>\n<p>Judi dengan hadiah uang merupakan hal illegal di Jepang. Walaupun berprinsip sebagai mesin judi tapi para pemilik dan pengusaha tempat pachinko dapat mengakali hukum di Jepang tadi. Pemain pachinko yang memenangi bola-bola besi mini saat bermain pachinko dapat menukarkan bola-bola besi mereka dengan sejumlah hadiah berbentuk barang seperti sabun, handuk, dan berbagai benda lain. Ingin menukar bola-bola pachinko dengan uang? Tidak bisa!</p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46197\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46197\" data-attachment-id=\"46197\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo-3/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko3.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Tukarkan bola-bola pachinko yang dimenangkan di counter dengan berbagai hadiah. Sumber: TheWeek\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Tukarkan bola-bola pachinko yang dimenangkan di counter dengan berbagai hadiah. Sumber: TheWeek&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko3-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko3.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46197\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko3.jpg\" alt=\"Tukarkan bola-bola pachinko yang dimenangkan di counter dengan berbagai hadiah. Sumber: TheWeek\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko3.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko3-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46197\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Tukarkan bola-bola pachinko yang dimenangkan di counter dengan berbagai hadiah. Sumber: TheWeek</p></div></p>\n<p>Kecuali “main belakang”. Karena sulit dibantah adanya praktek demikian (penukaran bola pachinko dengan uang tunai oleh pemilik mesin pachinko) walau hal ini jelas illegal dan dilakukan sembunyi-sembunyi.</p>\n<p>Sebelum era millennium baru, “<em>Pachislot Parlor</em>” alias tempat bermain pachinko merupakan tempat nongkrong kelompok usia paruh baya hingga manula; di mana mereka menghabiskan uang dan waktu di mesin pachinko sebagai sarana hiburan. Tapi kini semakin hari, pamor <em>pachislot parlor</em> semakin memudar.</p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46198\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46198\" data-attachment-id=\"46198\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo-4/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko4.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Sebuah suasana Pachislot Parlor di Jepang. Sumber: SoraNews\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Sebuah suasana Pachislot Parlor di Jepang. Sumber: SoraNews&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko4-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko4.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46198\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko4.jpg\" alt=\"Sebuah suasana Pachislot Parlor di Jepang. Sumber: SoraNews\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko4.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko4-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46198\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Sebuah suasana Pachislot Parlor di Jepang. Sumber: SoraNews</p></div></p>\n<p>Lembaga survey <em>Yano Research Institute Tokyo</em> mengumumkan hasil survey mereka soal keberadaan <em>pachinko parlor</em> di seluruh Jepang. Hingga Desember 2017 ada 10,258 tempat bermain pachinko di Jepang. Banyak? Bisa jadi. Tapi ada 420 tempat yang tutup sepanjang tahun 2017, yang artinya satu dari 25 tempat bermain pachinko tutup toko di Jepang. Sementara dari sisi pengusaha operasional pachinko, 177 dinyatakan bangkrut dan menyisakan 3,244 pengusaha. Dalam persentase, ini senilai 5% dari total pengusaha pachinko.</p>\n<p>Pengusaha pachinko tentu berusaha menjaga agar pemain pachinko tetap betah menggunakan mesin mereka. Salah satu cara adalah dengan men-digitalisasi mesin pachinko sehingga lebih menarik, seperti menambahkan layar HD, tema anime atau <em>game</em>, serta <em>sound effect</em> yang keren. Seperti misalnya mesin pachinko buatan Konami, yang menggunakan tema Castlevania. Tujuannya tentu agar memikat pemain usia muda; karena citra pachinko kini lebih ke “mainan orang tua”. Jauh dari kesan awal mesin itu diciptakan, yaitu sebagai mainan anak-anak.</p>\n<p><div id=\"attachment_46199\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-46199\" data-attachment-id=\"46199\" data-permalink=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/news/permainan-pachinko-jepang-menuju-kepunahan/attachment/a-worker-holds-silver-pachinko-balls-at-a-pachinko-parlour-in-fukaya-north-of-tokyo-5/\" data-orig-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko5.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"608,320\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;REUTERS&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo July 15, 2014. Japan&#039;s once-booming pachinko industry, grappling with a greying customer base and the threat of new competition from casinos, is adopting a softer touch and smoke-free zones to lure a new generation of players, particularly women. Pachinko, a modified version of pinball, is a fading national obsession, with about 12,000 parlours nation-wide and one in thirteen people playing the game. But that figure is declining as the population shrinks and younger people prefer games on their mobile phones. Picture taken July 15, 2014. REUTERS\\/Issei Kato (JAPAN - Tags: SOCIETY BUSINESS)\\r\\rATTENTION EDITORS PICTURE 14 OF 26 FOR PACKAGE &#039;JAPAN&#039;S PACHINKO PARLOURS&#039;\\rSEARCH &#039;KATO PACHINKO&#039; FOR ALL IMAGES&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1408406400&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;A worker holds silver pachinko balls at a pachinko parlour in Fukaya, north of Tokyo&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Mesin Pachinko bernuansa video game populer Castlevania dari Konami. Sumber: Pachinko-Club\" data-image-description=\"&lt;p&gt;Mesin Pachinko bernuansa video game populer Castlevania dari Konami. Sumber: Pachinko-Club&lt;/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko5-300x158.jpg\" data-large-file=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko5.jpg\" class=\"size-full wp-image-46199\" src=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko5.jpg\" alt=\"Mesin Pachinko bernuansa video game populer Castlevania dari Konami. Sumber: Pachinko-Club\" width=\"608\" height=\"320\" srcset=\"https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko5.jpg 608w, https://ervandra.github.io/ciayoblog/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/pachinko5-300x158.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-46199\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Mesin Pachinko bernuansa video game populer Castlevania dari Konami. Sumber: Pachinko-Club</p></div></p>\n<p>Jika kamu pergi ke Jepang, jangan lupa sempatkan diri mencoba mesin pachinko! Dan rasakan sensasi <em>“legal gambling</em>” yang diberikan oleh mesin itu.</p>\n<p><div 